text.tspan: Second pillar focuses on the seamless movement through the
space. It includes considerations like traffic patterns, furniture
arrangement, door and window placement, and sight lines.
Good flow makes navigating the space feel natural and effortless,
preventing any awkward bottlenecks or confusing layouts.
This is where the artistic side of interior design comes in. It
encompasses the visual appearance of the space, including
everything from color palettes and materials to furniture styles
and decorative elements. A successful aesthetic creates a
pleasing and harmonious environment that reflects the desired
mood and personality of the space.
